replies.body:
Not odd exceptions but basicly all juggernauts, tanks , some skirmishers and most fighters. Their job is to take out 'mispositioned' low healt targets,be it squisies like mages and marksmen or wounded frontliners. Yes most assassins make great splitpushers but not because they can 1v1 everyone like a juggernaut but because of their great mobility.

Oke now onto karthus v fizz. Ofcourse you dont pick him into fizz but if you get counterpicked the lvl1 is of utmost importance. You will always have to play safe and towerhugg from lvl 6 onwards but if you only do that with your low ms and no hard cc he will still dive and kill you every time his ult is up. You need to play agresssive at lvl 1 and keep him poked down so you can build a little advantage the first few lvls so you will atleast stand a chance to survive the rest of the laningphase.

Your original claim was that every assassin needs to be a lane bully the entire game in order for them to function. Some assassins have a weak earlygame as an intended weakness. Wether its just lvl 1 to 5 like {{champion:84}} {{champion:105}} or even the extreem case like {{champion:38}}
